# Changelog V.0.0.2.0

## Feb 15 - Big Refactor 

- update the file extension as a text instead of a application type
- Added a WIP `install.sh` script
- Refactor the `packages` folder into two subfolder : `windows` and `linux`
- Update the `windows` installer documentations
- Removed outdated files
- Added experimental `Makkefile.toml` file for cargo-make utility
- Add `install.sh`and `iscc.sh` for better Windows compiling support on GNU/Linux
- Added some file for vscode 
- Slighty update the logo by removing the extra white line
- Updated the `features` (`features.rs`) and `data::colors` (`data/features.rs`) crate for better readibiliy. 

## Feb 15

- Added custom .ascii file for GNU/Linux based OS
- Add a icon for the arch package
- added start of windows-cross-compile option 
- finally fix the bug where it still search for a file even if a other argument was present
 
## Feb 14 

- Remove duplicate or useless binary file like a duplicate `icon.ico` file and a complied `flex.exe` executable
- Update the `Cargo.lock` file
- Update the `README.md`
- Update the `.ascii` files
- Updated the cargo app image installer script
- Refactor the whole program into more modular with "crates"
- Add initial locale support with the rust crate rust-i18n 3
- Upgrade to Rust 2024 (expriemental)
- Update the `Cargo.toml` file with more info and updated version (0.0.2.0, in cargo.toml it is 0.0.20 due to technical reason)
- Updated the windows installed docs
- Add a vscode debugger option
- Added a git variant for the AUR
- update pkgbuild + license